<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Jesus, stop your whining</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tempra[CC]">Tempra[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:11 p.m. 19/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Jesus, stop your whining<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1530" TARGET=_self>TheBlack[BCK]</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I've returned more peoples corpses then you could even imagine. You are obbssessed with us, get over it. Yes you probably did something to us and we killed you, sorry.. yada yada yada

<P>thanks for the comment on the guild to be feared... i like that
<P>Tempra[CC] "Thou caneth roleplayeth tooeth!" :)
<P>&gt; I doubt this will be corrected. It is seen as a way of keeping
<BR>&gt; you on your toes in battle. You have to remember to hit
<BR>&gt; "a" before targeting another member of your group for
<BR>&gt; healing or buffing, and then hit "a" again when you go
<BR>&gt; back to your target. I agree with you, but I doubt Verant will
<BR>&gt; because it's too easily explainable and avoidable to be fixed.
<P>&gt; This I completely disagree with you on. When you hide, you are
<BR>&gt; not sure if you are hidden well enough to conceal your body from
<BR>&gt; everyone. You might THINK you are hidden, but others around you
<BR>&gt; might be able to detect you. As for the ability to spot hidden
<BR>&gt; players, this SHOULD be dependent on observer. Some people are
<BR>&gt; just more acute, more able to spot things, more observant, etc.
<BR>&gt; You should make a roll to see if you can spot a hidden player.
<P>&gt; As for your willingness to stake your life on it, that should be
<BR>&gt; dependent on your skill level. If you have a 50% skill level,
<BR>&gt; you know you will succeed half the time. That's a gamble, but if
<BR>&gt; you're running from 10 guys, it's a gamble you might take. If
<BR>&gt; your skill is an 80 or 90, I'd stake my life on that any time.
<P>&gt; Agree here. Looting is a serious problem. CC, or should I say
<BR>&gt; "THE Guild to fear on the PVP server," just loves
<BR>&gt; hanging around until they can get their hands on some free armor
<BR>&gt; or some gold.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
